{"id": "EUVD-2025-30844", "enisaUuid": "13fca270-5cdd-3e5c-8a14-6cd8ced9ae92", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/mediatek: fix potential OF node use-after-free\n\nThe for_each_child_of_node() helper drops the reference it takes to each\nnode as it iterates over children and an explicit of_node_put() is only\nneeded when exiting the loop early.\n\nDrop the recently introduced bogus additional reference count decrement\nat each iteration that could potentially lead to a use-after-free.", "datePublished": "2025-09-23T06:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-12T21:31:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39882", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4de37a48b6b58faaded9eb765047cf0d8785ea18", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b2fbe0f9f80b9cfa1e06ddcf8b863d918394ef1d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b58a26cdd4795c1ce6a80e38e9348885555dacd6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c4901802ed1ce859242e10af06e6a7752cba0497"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39882", "GHSA-wpx2-5m46-33qp"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "037574f5-b297-31a0-bf88-adbb999d2037", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "15fc70bf-51c9-38db-93fd-512b33d0d9ce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17-rc6"}, {"id": "4660f7c5-72e2-3770-869a-8e32f6ee0c1b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.16.5 <6.16.8"}, {"id": "518734d5-fde2-3237-b5e0-0ae70bb03cd7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12.45 <6.12.48"}, {"id": "581134d5-4043-35c7-bed1-0bb1e13c27d5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "31ce7c089b50c3d3056c37e0e25e7535e4428ae1 <b58a26cdd4795c1ce6a80e38e9348885555dacd6"}, {"id": "86d36bf4-bf61-3175-aea5-db1b6c7b70f1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.17-rc4"}, {"id": "87de98e5-85f0-3d03-92ec-6ba1da901779", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.107"}, {"id": "b14ca